AttributeList.Text: This block is for the interlocking and starting of Across-the-line non-reversing starters.

This network handles the simulation of the motor starter.
IF SimulationMode and GlobalSimulation are FALSE, then the Start and Stop requests from the HMI are passed to the StartRequestHMI and StopRequestHMI Bits.
IF SimulationMode or GlobalSimulation = TRUE, then the logic uses the SimulationStartRequest and SimulationStopRequest to enable and Disable the SimulatedStart and SimulatedStop bits.

Logic for processing the Start and Stop Commands.
The Start & StopRequestHMI as well as the Start & StopPB_Local bits are sent through a Oneshot to prevent the StartRequest and StopRequest from being held on as TRUE.
